articles.title: Tariffs thaw, rivalry simmers: U.S.–China trade truce enters uneasy phase
articles.description: Even as a U.S.–China trade truce appears to be holding, analysts caution that the détente remains fragile in a rivalry increasingly defined by strategic competition.

articles.title: AMD's Lisa Su sees 35% annual sales growth driven by 'insatiable' AI demand
articles.description: Su said that AMD could be able to achieve "double-digit" share in the data center AI chip market over the next three to five years.

articles.title: If the Supreme Court orders Trump to repay tariffs, U.S. importers say it wouldn't be 'messy'
articles.description: U.S. Customs has collected nearly $200 billion in tariffs since the beginning of 2025. The Supreme Court has raised concerns about the process of repaying them.

articles.title: Trump floats $2,000 tariff rebate checks: Here's what you need to know
articles.description: President Donald Trump refloated the idea of tariff rebate checks over the weekend, but experts say such a plan is unlikely to become policy.

articles.title: The shutdown put jobs and inflation data on hold. Here's when it could be back — and what it might say
articles.description: Economic data releases — payroll and jobs reports, CPI and PPI — have lagged during the government shutdown and likely will take some time to get rolling again.

articles.title: Mark Cuban: The job-hunting advice I give my own kids in the age of AI—it'll make their careers 'easier' and more successful
articles.description: If you're looking for an entry-level job in the age of AI, seek jobs at small- to medium-sized businesses over ones at large corporations, says Mark Cuban.

articles.title: 'Ghost job' postings are adding another layer of uncertainty to the stalling jobs picture
articles.description: Since the beginning of 2024, job openings have outnumbered hires by more than 2.2 million a month.
